Mac-specific changes in this repo
---------------------------------

1. Configs (evo2/configs/*.yml)
   - use_flash_attn:               True -> False  (SDPA fallback works on MPS)
   - use_fp8_input_projections:    True -> False  (Transformer Engine is CUDA-only)

2. evo2/models.py
   - Device auto-detection (CUDA > MPS > CPU).
   - Model moved to detected device; inputs moved to model device.
   - Unpacks (logits, inference_params_dict) tuple from StripedHyena.
   - Expands FP8 fallback to include 1B model name (not just 7B).

3. evo2/scoring.py
   - Device auto-detection helper.
   - device= defaults to None and is resolved at call time.

4. patches/patch_vortex.py (runtime patch applied to the installed `vtx`
   package, which exposes `vortex.model.*`)
   - engine.py:     torch.autocast("cuda")          -> device-aware autocast
   - engine.py:     torch.fft.fft().repeat()        -> .unsqueeze().expand()
                    (MPS doesn't support .repeat() on complex tensors)
   - generation.py: torch.cuda.memory_allocated(d)  -> torch.memory_allocated(d)
   - model.py:      torch.cuda.empty_cache()        -> device-aware empty_cache

Models known to run on Mac (MPS)
--------------------------------

  evo2_1b_base          ~4 GB    works on 16 GB Macs
  evo2_7b_base          ~14 GB   needs 32 GB+ unified memory
  evo2_7b               ~14 GB   needs 32 GB+ unified memory
  evo2_7b_262k          ~14 GB   needs 32 GB+ unified memory
  evo2_7b_microviridae  ~14 GB   needs 32 GB+ unified memory

Models that cannot run on Mac
-----------------------------

  evo2_20b, evo2_40b, evo2_40b_base
    Require FP8 via NVIDIA Transformer Engine (Hopper-class GPUs only).
    This is a hardware/runtime constraint, not just a memory one.
